Turkeyâ€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell for a second day, declining less than 0.1 percent to
62,444.93 at the close in Istanbul.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Banvit Bandirma Vitaminli Yem Sanayii AS (BANVT)  , a
Turkish poultry producer, climbed for a second day, adding 0.5
percent to 4.14 liras. The company purchased a poultry complex
in the eastern province of Elazig for 12.3 million liras ($6.8
million), it said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange
after the market closed yesterday.  Netas Telekomunikasyon AS (NETAS)  , an Istanbul-based
maker of telecommunications equipment, plunged 14 percent to 147
liras, the steepest drop in more than 3 1/2 years, after one of
its owners put up shares for sale. Oep Rhea  Turkey  Tech BV,
which controls 3.15 million shares in Netas, or a 48.6 percent
stake, registered 744,123 shares for sale, according to a
regulatory filing from owner Rhea Girism Sermayesi Ortakligi AS
after the market closed yesterday. Oep Rhea also recorded
366,684 Netas shares for sale on May 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
